The body of eight-year-old Tazne Van Wyk has been found outside Worcester in the Western Cape. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The body of Tazne Van Wyk (8) has been found outside Worcester in the Western Cape. One suspect, Moehydien Pangaker (54), was arrested on Monday in Cradock, Eastern Cape. Police Spokesperson Brigadier Novela Potelwa says the body was discovered in a storm water drain on Thursday night after a lead from the 54-year-old suspect. READ: Lesufi to release forensic report into Enock Mpianzi's death The 54-year-old appeared briefly in court on Tuesday and was remanded in custody. She went missing two weeks ago from her Elsies River home outside Cape Town. Listen to the full interview with Police Spokesperson Brigadier Novela Potelwa above.